body:
Would it be possible to get a rule that detect the case when the packed dimension of signal is assigned with array notation (`'{}`)?

Example code that should trigger warning:
```verilog
module foo;
  wire [1:0] bar;
  assign bar = '{1'b0, 1'b1};        // Should give lint error
endmodule
```

We want to write the code like this:
```verilog
module foo;
  wire [1:0] bar;
  assign bar = {1'b0, 1'b1};
endmodule
```
